== Bio

Rad Niazadeh is currently a Motwani postdoctoral fellow at Stanford University, Department of Computer Science, where he is hosted by Amin Saberi, Tim Roughgarden, and Moses Charikar. Prior to Stanford, he obtained his Ph.D. in Computer Science from Cornell University under Bobby Kleinberg. He is joining Chicago Booth as an assistant professor in July 2020. Before that, he will be a visiting researcher at Google Research NYC from Dec 2019. His research interests are broadly at the intersection of algorithms, game theory and machine learning, with a focus on applications in market design and revenue management. 

== Highlights

For my research, I have been awarded the [https://connect.informs.org/rmp/awards/dissertation-award INFORMS Revenue Management & Pricing Dissertation Award (Honorable Mention)], [http://googleresearch.blogspot.com/2016/03/announcing-2016-google-phd-fellows-for.html Google Ph.D. Fellowship (market algorithms)], [http://news.cornell.edu/stories/2006/11/alumni-irwin-and-joan-jacobs-give-30-million-gift Jacobs Scholar Fellowship (Cornell)] and [https://windowsontheory.org/2016/12/25/motwani-postdoctoral-fellowship-at-stanford/ Motwani Fellowship (Stanford)]. During my Ph.D. study, I have been fortunate to be research intern at [https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/group/theory-group/ Microsoft Research (Redmond)], [https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/lab/microsoft-research-new-england/ Microsoft Research (New England)] and [https://research.yahoo.com/ Yahoo! Research].\n\n
